1 (c) A written exemption order issued under subsection (b) of this section
2 shall:
3 (1) not be valid for more than one year;
4 (2) specify the neonicotinoid pesticides, uses, and crops, or plants to
5 which the exemption order applies; the date on which the exemption order
6 takes effect; the exemption order’s duration; and the exemption order’s
7 geographic scope, which may include specific farms, fields, or properties; and
8 (3) provide a detailed evaluation determining that an agricultural
9 emergency or an environmental emergency exists.
10 (d) A written exemption order issued under subsection (b) of this section
11 may:
12 (1) establish restrictions related to the use of neonicotinoid pesticides to
13 which the exemption order applies to minimize harm to pollinator populations,
14 bird populations, ecosystem health, and public health; or
15 (2) establish other restrictions related to the use of neonicotinoid
16 pesticides to which the exemption order applies that the Secretary of
17 Agriculture, Food and Markets considers necessary.
